papers?id=lm0xAAAAIBAJ&sjid=VwMEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6650,4748310&dq= Gunman attacks school, kills himself], ''[[Toledo Blade]]'' (September 18, 1993)</ref><ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=bR0PAAAAIBAJ&sjid=4oQDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5130,5790941&dq= Suicide note says Wyoming gunman \"evil\"], ''[[The Deseret News]]'' (September 27, 1993)</ref>\n|-\n| September 17, 1993\n| [[Darien, Illinois]], United States\n| Phillip Powell, 15\n| 1 dead\n| \n| 15-year-old Phillip Powell killed Barrett Modisette (17) at the Hinsdale South High School parking lot. Powell was a self-described gang member who shot Barrett because Barrett was protecting his younger brother from Powell's verbal bullying. Powell was tried as an adult and was sentenced to 37 years in prison in 1994.<ref>[http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1994-07-27/news/9407270381_1_student-s-death-gang-violence-sentenced 16-year-old Killer Gets 37 Years], \u2018\u2019[[Chicago Tribune]]\u2019\u2019 (July 27, 1994)</ref>\n|-\n| October 6, 1993\n| [[Hausleiten]], Austria\n| ..., 13\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| A 13-year-old student, waiting at the entrance of the [[Hauptschule]] in Hausleiten, shot and wounded the principal of the school with a rifle before committing suicide. The student was caught smoking the day before and the principal told the boy he had to inform his parents about it.<ref>[http://diepresse.com/home/panorama/oesterreich/310346/index.do?direct=310340&_vl_backlink=/home/panorama/index.do&selChannel= Gewehr, Revolver, Messer im Klassenzimmer], ''[[Die Presse]]'' (June 13, 2007)</ref>\n|-\n| December 1, 1993\n| [[Wauwatosa, Wisconsin]], United States\n| Leonard McDowell, 21\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Leonard McDowell, a 21-year-old former student at [[Wauwatosa West High School]], shot Associate Principal Dale Breitlow three times with a .44-cal. Taurus revolver in a second-floor hallway. McDowell was found guilty of the murder and sane at the time of the shooting. His life sentence was upheld by the state Court of Appeals in April, 1997.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.jsonline.com/story/index.aspx?id=506749|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071014115039/http://www.jsonline.com/story/index.aspx?id=506749|url-status=dead|title=Milwaukee - home|archivedate=October 14, 2007}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 17, 1993\n| [[Chelsea, Michigan]], United States\n| Stephen Leith\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| Steve Leith, a science teacher at [[Chelsea High School (Michigan)|Chelsea High School]] walked into a staff meeting being held at the school and shot and killed the district superintendent and wounded the school principal and a teacher. Leith was then arrested by police.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1993/12/17/us/police-arrest-a-teacher-in-school-shootings.html |title=Police Arrest a Teacher in School Shootings |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1993-12-17 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=pOsVAAAAIBAJ&sjid=5hQEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6924,418870&dq=chelsea+michigan+school&hl=en |title=Teacher arrested in school shootings |publisher=News.google.ca |date=1993-12-17 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 31, 1994\n| [[Seattle, Washington]], United States\n| Darrell Cloud, 24\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 24-year-old Darrell Cloud entered Whitman Middle School and shot his former teacher, 45-year-old Neal Summers, to death. Cloud would serve nine years in prison for the murder. The motive for the shooting was sexual abuse that was alleged to have been perpetrated by Summers against Cloud since Cloud was 13 years old.<ref>{{cite news|last=Shaw |first=Linda |url=http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/localnews/2002162113_cloud26m.html |title=Abuse victim who killed teacher settles with district |publisher=Seattletimes.nwsource.com |date=2005-01-27 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 1, 1994\n| [[Boonville, Missouri]], United States\n| Dante D. Hayes, 33\n| 2 dead\n| \n| Dante D. Hayes, 33, a hunter and ex-convict, shot and killed Richard Vancena, 58, a c