23.html?dids=18589823:18589823&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Jan+06%2C+1995&author=Paul+Duggan%3B+Wendy+Melillo&pub=The+Washington+Post+(pre-1997+Fulltext)&desc=Student+Fatally+Shot+at+Cardozo+High%3B+D.C.+Police+Say+Suspect+Is+Youth%2C+14&pqatl=google|title=Student Fatally Shot at Cardozo High; D.C. Police Say Suspect Is Youth, 14|first=Paul|last=Duggan|date=January 6, 1995}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 12, 1995\n| [[Seattle, Washington]], United States\n| ..., 15\n| \n| 2 injured\n| A 15-year-old [[Garfield High School (Seattle, Washington)|Garfield High School]] student left school during the day and returned with his grandfather's 9mm semiautomatic handgun. He wounded two students.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thestranger.com/seattle/the-shooter/Content?oid=13491|title=The Shooter|newspaper=The Stranger|author=Eli Sanders|date=2003-03-05}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 1, 1995\n| [[Charlotte Amalie, United States Virgin Islands]], United States\n| Nashibo George, 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Lamar Knight is stabbed to death by fellow student Nashibo George after a fight at Charlotte Amalie High School. Nashibo George is found guilty of [[voluntary manslaughter]] on February 20, 2004.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vid.uscourts.gov/dcopinion/97cr0084.pdf |title=Memorandum Opinion |format=PDF |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716140546/http://www.vid.uscourts.gov/dcopinion/97cr0084.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-16 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.virginislandsdailynews.com/index.pl/article_home?id=1986887|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20051028214708/http://www.virginislandsdailynews.com/index.pl/article_home?id=1986887|url-status=dead|title=Virgin Islands, Virgin Islands Newspaper, A Pulitzer Prize Winning Ne\u2026|date=28 October 2005|archivedate=28 October 2005|website=virginislandsdailynews.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| August 29, 1995\n| [[Laredo, Texas]], United States\n| Jonah Iverson, 12\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 12-year-old Jonah Iverson