TU|date=June 29, 2006|accessdate=February 1, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Teenager faces charges in Oregon high school shooting\n|url=http://seattletimes.com/html/localnews/2002826654_weboreshooting24.html|newspaper=Seattle Times|date=February 24, 2006|accessdate=February 1, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 14, 2006\n| [[Reno]], [[Nevada]], United States\n| James Scott Newman, 14\n|\n| 2 injured\n| [[Pine Middle School shooting]]. 14-year-old student James Newman brought a [[.38 ACP|.38-caliber]] [[revolver]] to Pine Middle School in [[Reno]], [[Nevada]], and shot and injured two students at random in the school's hallway before being restrained by a physical education teacher.<ref name=\"KOLOTV\">{{cite news\n|first = Koula\n|last = Gianulias\n|author2=Kara Tsuboi |author3=Ed Pearce\n |title = Reno School Shooting Team Report\n|url = http://www.kolotv.com/home/headlines/2461261.html\n|work=\n|publisher= [[KOLO-TV]]\n|location = [[Reno, Nevada]], United States\n|accessdate = 2008-11-21\n }}</ref><ref name=\"LasVegasReview\">{{cite news\n|first = Sandra\n|last = Chereb\n|author2=Kara Tsuboi |author3=Ed Pearce\n |title = School shooting arraignment delayed in school\n|url = http://www.reviewjournal.com/lvrj_home/2006/Mar-18-Sat-2006/news/6431035.html\n|agency = [[The Associated Press]]\n|work= [[Las Vegas Review-Journal]]\n|publisher= Sherman Frederick\n|location = [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], United States\n|date = 2006-03-18\n|accessdate = 2008-11-21\n|quote =\n }}</ref> Newman was charged as a juvenile for two counts of [[Battery (crime)|battery]] with a deadly weapon and was sentenced to [[house arrest]] and 200 hours of [[community service]].<ref name=\"WashingtonPost\">{{cite news\n|first = Scott\n|last = Sonner\n|title = Teen Gets House Arrest in Nev. Shooting\n|url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/05/26/AR2006052602039_Technorati.html\n|work= [[The Washington Post]]\n|publisher= [[Katharine Weymouth]]\n|location = Washington, D.C., United 