un [[Lead shot|pellet]] during the ordeal. The gunman is suspected to be a 16-year-old student of the school, Bryan Oliver. Cleveland and the other student that was shot at are both believed to be intended targets of the gunman. On January 14, Oliver was charged with two counts of attempted murder and assault with a firearm.<ref>[http://www.wptv.com/dpp/news/national/taft-high-school-shooting-update-reports-indicate-at-least-2-people-shot-in-california-high-school Taft High School shooting update: Reports indicate at least 1 person shot in California high school] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130112232551/http://www.wptv.com/dpp/news/national/taft-high-school-shooting-update-reports-indicate-at-least-2-people-shot-in-california-high-school |date=2013-01-12 }} Retrieved January 10, 2013</ref><ref name=usatoday>{{cite news|last=Winter|first=Michael|author2=Stanglin, Doug |title=Calif. teen with shotgun wounds classmate in school|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2013/01/10/taft-california-shooting-high-school/1823539/|work=[[USA Today]]|publisher=January 10, 2013|accessdate=January 10, 2013|date=January 10, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 12, 2013\n| [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]], United States\n| \n| \n| 1 injured\n| A 16-year-old boy was shot in a field across the school campus after a basketball game was held at [[Osborn High School]]. He was hospitalized in serious condition.<ref name=detroitcbslocal>{{cite web|title=Teen Shot After High School Basketball Game|url=http://detroit.cbslocal.com/2013/01/12/teen-shot-after-high-school-basketball-game/|work=[[CBS]]|publisher=January 12, 2013|accessdate=January 15, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|January 16, 2013}}\n|{{sort|Spring Township, Berks County, Pennsylvania}}, United States\n|14-year-old male student \n|<span style=\"display:none\">0,000,001</span>\n|<span style=\"display:none\">0,000,001</span>1 injured\n|A 14-year-old male student stabbed another 14-year-old male student four times with a pocke