nard McDowell, a 21-year-old former student at [[Wauwatosa West High School]], shot Associate Principal Dale Breitlow three times with a .44-cal. Taurus revolver in a second-floor hallway. McDowell was found guilty of the murder and sane at the time of the shooting. His life sentence was upheld by the state Court of Appeals in April, 1997.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.jsonline.com/story/index.aspx?id=506749|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071014115039/http://www.jsonline.com/story/index.aspx?id=506749|url-status=dead|title=Milwaukee - home|archivedate=October 14, 2007}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 17, 1993\n| [[Chelsea, Michigan]], United States\n| Stephen Leith\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| Steve Leith, a science teacher at [[Chelsea High School (Michigan)|Chelsea High School]] walked into a staff meeting being held at the school and shot and killed the district superintendent and wounded the school principal and a teacher. Leith was then arrested by police.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1993/12/17/us/police-arrest-a-teacher-in-school-shootings.html |title=Police Arrest a Teacher in School Shootings |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1993-12-17 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=pOsVAAAAIBAJ&sjid=5hQEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6924,418870&dq=chelsea+michigan+school&hl=en |title=Teacher arrested in school shootings |publisher=News.google.ca |date=1993-12-17 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 31, 1994\n| [[Seattle, Washington]], United States\n| Darrell Cloud, 24\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 24-year-old Darrell Cloud entered Whitman Middle School and shot his former teacher, 45-year-old Neal Summers, to death. Cloud would serve nine years in prison for the murder. The motive for the shooting was sexual abuse that was alleged to have been perpetrated by Summers against Cloud since Cloud was 13 years old.<ref>{{cite news|last=Shaw |first=Linda |url=http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/localnews/2002162113_cloud26m.html |titl