lying\u2019|date=2007-12-12|url =http://hindustantimes.com/StoryPage/StoryPage.aspx?id=df416321-98a6-4572-b0bf-c6c5fbf29902&MatchID1=4604&TeamID1=6&TeamID2=7&MatchType1=1&SeriesID1=1157&MatchID2=4575&TeamID3=8&TeamID4=2&MatchType2=1&SeriesID2=1147&PrimaryID=4604&Headline=School+students+shoot+classmate+for+%e2%80%98bullying%e2%80%99|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|accessdate = 2009-04-25}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 21, 2007\n| [[Union City, California|Union City]],<br>[[California]],<br>United States\n| Unknown\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Vernon Matthew Eddins, a 14-year-old student of [[James Logan High School]], was shot dead at the doorstep of Barnard-White Middle School, in [[Union City, California]].<ref name=\"usatodayviolencemap\">{{cite news|title=Mapping school violence|date=2009-04-12|agency= [[Associated Press]]|url =https://www.usatoday.com/news/nation/graphic-school-killings.htm|work=[[USA Today]]|accessdate = 2009-05-03}}</ref><ref name=\"baycitychronicle1221\">{{cite news|title=Boy shot dead in front of middle school |date=2007-12-21 |url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?file=/baycitynews/archive/2007/12/21/unioncity21.DTL&tsp=1 |work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]] |accessdate=2009-05-11 |url-status=dead |first=Bay |last=City |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071225145824/http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?file=%2Fbaycitynews%2Farchive%2F2007%2F12%2F21%2Funioncity21.DTL&tsp=1 |archivedate=December 25, 2007 }}</ref> Police issued that the shooting was prompted by an argument escalating between [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Latino]] and [[African American]] groups of teenagers. No suspects were ever sought.<ref name=\"yollinchronicle1223\">{{cite news|first=Patricia|last=Yollin|title=Boy shot near middle school IDd|date=2007-12-23|url =http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article/article?f=/c/a/2007/12/23/BADIU3PC9.DTL|work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]]|accessdate = 2009-05-11}}</ref><ref name=\"ktvu1222\">{{cite news|title=Victim Of Union City Shooting Was A St