i Vantaggiato, 68\n| 1 dead\n| 5 injured\n|[[2012 Brindisi school bombing]]. A three gas cylinder bomb hidden in a large rubbish bin exploded in front of the Morvillo Falcone high school in Brindisi, Italy, killing one 16-year-old female student and injuring five others \u2013 one seriously. The bomber was identified and arrested on June 6.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-18128170|title=School bomb kills girl in Italy|date=19 May 2012|publisher=|via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bari.repubblica.it/cronaca/2012/05/19/news/attentato_esplosivo_in_una_scuola_quattro_strudenti_feriti_a_brindisi_l_esplosione_nell_istituto_professionale_nei_pressi_-35438304/|title=La cronaca / Bomba a Brindisi, dolore e rabbia Fischi ai politici: \"Ora ammazzateci tutti\" - Bari - Repubblica.it|website=Bari - La Repubblica}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 25, 2012\n| [[Sankt Poelten]], [[Austria]]\n| Unidentified male, 37\n| 1 dead \n| 1 injured\n| Shortly after 8:00 local time, an armed 37-year-old man broke into Volksschule Wagram in Sankt Poelten, [[Austria]] and hauled his two children out of the classroom. His daughter managed to escape, which promoted him to take his 8-year-old son to a cloakroom and shot him in the head, critically injuring him. The father then escaped from the school in a car, and later committed suicide after he crashed his car on a local farm road. The most likely motive of his actions is that he wanted to get revenge on his wife.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://diepresse.com/home/panorama/oesterreich/761026/Schule_Vater-schiesst-Sohn-in-den-Kopf|title=Schule: Vater schie\u00dft Sohn in den Kopf|website=diepresse.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| August 16, 2012\n| [[Memphis, Tennessee]], United States\n| \n|\n| 2 injured\n| Two Hamilton High School students were shot and wounded in the parking lot of the school. The attack was believed to be gang-related.<ref>{{cite news|last=Carroll |first=Scott|url=http://www.commercialappeal.com/news/2012/aug/16/crime-report-woman-shot-in-argument-over-5-loan/?partner=RSS |title=CRIME REPORT: Students involved in gang-related shooting outside Hamilton High School |newspaper=Commercial Appeal |date=August 16, 2012 |accessdate=January 15, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|August 27, 2012}}\n|{{sort|Perry Hall, Maryland}}, United States\n|Robert Wayne Gladden, Jr., 15\n|<span style=\"display:none\">0,000,001</span>\n|<span style=\"display:none\">0,000,001</span>1 injured\n| Robert Gladden, 15, took a [[double barrel shotgun]] to [[Perry Hall High School]] and fired shots inside the school cafeteria. A 17-year-old senior with [[Down syndrome]] was hit in the lower back while he was sitting at a table and suffered critical wounds. Gladden was immediately subdued by two school faculty members, and was arrested. He was tried as an adult for attempted murder and was sentenced to 35 years in prison.<ref>{{cite web|last=Knezevich |first=Alison |url=http://www.wgntv.com/entertainment/tv/bs-md-co-gladden-indictment-20120904,0,2209931.story |title=Robert Gladden Jr. indicted in Perry Hall school shooting\u2014WGN |publisher=Wgntv.com |date=2012-09-04 |accessdate=2012-10-18 }}{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.com/baltimore-school-shooting-victim-downs-syndrome-134105244--abc-news-topstories.html |title=Alleged Baltimore School Shooter's Victim Has Down's Syndrome\u2014Yahoo! News |publisher=News.yahoo.com |date=2012-08-28 |accessdate=2012-10-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 7, 2012\n| [[Normal, Illinois]], United States\n| 14-year-old arrested\n|\n|\n| A 14-year-old student fired multiple gunshots in the ceiling of Normal Community High School, and was tackled by a teacher. Nobody was injured. The student was arrested and is charged with 16 felony counts.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/09/07/shots-fired-in-ill-school_n_1864888.html|title=Illinois School Shooting: Shots Fired In Normal Community Hig