ara Elizondo, opened fire in the Colegio Americano del Noreste classroom with a .22 caliber handgun. Federico committed suicide by shooting himself in the cheek.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://lopezdoriga.com/nacional/declaran-muerte-cerebral-al-menor-autor-del-ataque-en-escuela-monterrey/|title=The youngest author of the attack in Monterrey school declares brain death (Spanish)|work=[[Lopez Doriga Digital]]| date=18 January 2017| author=}}</ref> Students Ana Cecilia Ramos Luis and Fernando Martinez, both 14 years old, and 24-year-old teacher Cecilia Cristina Solis suffered serious head injuries; 15-year-old Manuel Chavez suffered an arm injury.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.sdpnoticias.com/local/nuevo-leon/2017/01/18/difunden-nombres-de-heridos-por-disparos-en-colegio-americano| title=Spread of names of gunshot wounded at American College (Spanish)|work=[[SDP Noticias]]| date=18 January 2017| author=}}</ref> Guevara had psychological problems.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2017/01/18/gunfire-erupts-at-mexican-private-school-injuries-reported.html| title=15-year-old student shoots teacher, 3 classmates at American school in Mexico|work=[[Fox News]] (World)| date=2 March 2016| author=}}</ref> Teacher Cecilia Cristina Solis died on March 29, 2017, hours after being declared brain dead.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.milenio.com/region/muere-maestra-baleada-colegio_americano_noreste-milenio-monterrey_0_928707377.html| title=Muere Maestra baleada en Colegio Americano del Noreste (Spanish)|work=[[Milenio]]| date=29 March 2017| author=}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|January 20, 2017}}\n|[[West Liberty, Ohio]], US \n| Student, 17\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A student was shot and injured by another student at [[West Liberty-Salem High School]].\n|-\n|{{Dts|March 16, 2017}}\n|[[Grasse, France]] \n| Kylian Barbey, 17 (charged)\n|\n| 4 injured\n| Kylian Barbey, a 17-year-old boy, armed with a [[rifle]], two [[handguns]], a [[revolver]] and two [[grenades]], opened fire at Alexis de Tocqueville high school. A total of four were injured, three students and the school's principal. Anti-terrorist commandos were sent to the scene and the shooter was arrested. The perpetrator's [[Facebook]] and [[YouTube]] accounts showed that he was interested in the [[Columbine Massacre]] and watched videos on how to make homemade weapons.<ref>{{cite web|author=<!--Not stated-->|title=Teenager held over French school shooting|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-39292755|website=BBC News|date=16 March 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|May 15, 2017}}\n|Guachipelin de Escazu, [[Costa Rica]]\n| Unknown group of assailants in van\n| 2 dead\n| 1 injured\n| A group of men in a van attempted to assassinate a Lebanese man while he was driving in the city. The man eventually drove onto Mount View School grounds, near the school's entrance, while under gunfire. Both the man and his bodyguard were killed, with the shooters driving off from the scene. In the gunfire, a student was left in critical condition after he was shot multiple times and run over by the shooter's van as it sped away. Firefighters were also called to the school to extinguish the burning wreckage of the targeted car. <ref>{{cite web|author=<!--Not stated-->|title= 2 Dead 1 Critical Escazu Private School Shooting|url=http://thecrpost.com/2017/05/15/escazu-private-school-shoot-out/|website=The CR Post|date=15 May 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|March 21, 2017}}\n|[[King City, California]], US \n| 17-year-old unnamed male \n|\n| 1 injured\n| An 18-year-old [[King City High School]] student was shot and critically wounded outside the school's auditorium. The gunman ran across the school's campus and baseball field, and fled the area. The school was then placed on lockdown.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ksbw.com/article/shooting-at-king-city-high-school-gunman-at-large/9163959|title=Photo released of suspect after King City High student shot|publisher=[[KSBW]]|date=March 21, 2017|author=Larson, Amy}}</ref> A suspe