amak. The attacker wounded three girls and a teacher, and set a classroom on fire.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/three-students-teacher-hospitalized-after-teen-attacks-school-in-russia/29174568.html|title=Three Students, Teacher Hospitalized After Teen Attacks School In Russia |date=April 18, 2018 |work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|April 20, 2018}}\n|[[Ocala, Florida]], United States\n| Sky Bouche, 19\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A former Forest High School student entered the school with a guitar case containing a 1930 sawed-off shotgun. He retrieved the gun in the washroom, and entered the hallway. Bouche was ready to fire and reportedly had seen multiple students, but had a strike of morality before firing. He later stated when the moment came, and he saw a female students distress in reaction to seeing him, he couldn't bring himself to hurt anyone. Instead he fired a shot at a nearby closed door, without aiming. He later claimed that he \"didn't think the gun would fire\". A 17-year-old male student in the classroom was wounded after he was shot in the ankle. Bouche then entered the classroom of one of his former teachers, and surrendered peacefully to the responding SRO. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ocala.com/news/20190420/one-year-after-shooting-at-ocalas-forest-high-school|title=One year after the shooting at Ocala\u2019s Forest High School |date=April 20, 2019 |work=OcalaStarBanner}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|April 27, 2018}}\n|[[Shaanxi]], China\n| Zhao, 28\n| 9 dead\n| 10 injured\n| Nine students were stabbed to death and 10 injured in a knife attack outside a school in northern China. The man who carried out the attack was reportedly a former student, taking revenge for having been bullied at the school. The dead were seven girls and two boys aged 12 to 15.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-43921567|title=China stabbings: Nine students killed in Shaanxi |date=April 28, 2018 |work=BBC News}}</ref>\n|-\n|May 25, 