an adult and a teenager. After the incident, the suspect came into custody.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/indiana-school-shooting-report-of-shots-fired-at-noblesville-west-middle-school/|title=Police: 2 injured in shooting at Noblesville West Middle School in Indiana|last=|first=|date=2018-05-18|work=CBS Interactive Inc.|access-date=2018-05-19|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n|October 17, 2018\n|[[Kerch]]\n| Vladislav Roslyakov, 18\n|21 dead\n|70 injured\n|The [[Kerch Polytechnic College massacre]]. An 18-year-old student at the [[Kerch Polytechnic College]] set off explosives in the school and began shooting, killing 20. The shooter was highly inspired by the [[Columbine High School Massacre]], even going as far as wearing the same clothes as one of the two shooters involved in that attack.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-45891201|title=Gun attack at Crimea college kills 19|date=October 17, 2018|via=www.bbc.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|December 17, 2018\n|[[Haridwar, Uttarakhand]], India\n| Student, 13\n| -\n|1 injured\n| DAV Public School shooting in Haridwar\n|-\n|February 11, 2019\n|[[Stowbtsy]], Belarus\n| Student, 15\n| 2 dead\n| 2 injured\n| A 15-year-old student stabbed a 50-year-old history teacher in the neck, who then died on the spot. He also stabbed two students, who tried to defend the teacher, injuring both of them. The assailant then left the class and entered a nearby classroom, where he stabbed a 17-year-old student, who also died on the spot.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/belarusian-teen-suspected-of-stabbing-teacher-classmate-to-death/29763228.html|title=Belarusian Teen Suspected Of Stabbing Teacher, Classmate To Death |date=February 11, 2019 |work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty}}</ref>\n|-\n|February 26, 2019\n|[[Toronto]], Ontario\n| Unknown\n| \n| 2 injured\n| A fight between two students ended off with a double stabbing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://toronto.citynews.ca/2019/02/26/stabbing-york-memorial-collegiate/|title=2 students stabbed outside York Memorial Collegiate Institute |date=February 26, 2019 |work=CityNews}}</ref>\n|-\n|March 13, 2019\n|[[Suzano]], Brazil\n| Guilherme Taucci Monteiro, 17; Luiz Henrique de Castro, 25\n| 10 dead\n| 11 injured\n| [[Suzano massacre|Two masked]] men shot and killed 6 students and 2 staff members at a public secondary school in Suzano, Brazil. Eleven additional victims were wounded. The suspects committed suicide inside the school.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/03/13/americas/brazil-school-shooting/index.html/|title=At least 8 people were killed in a school shooting in Brazil |date=March 13, 2019 |work=CNN}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 7, 2019\n| Colorado, United States\n| Devon Erickson, 18; Maya Elizabeth, 16\n| 1 dead\n| 8 injured\n| At the [[STEM School Highlands Ranch]] two suspects, who were students at the school, injured eight students and killed one.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/05/08/us/denver-stem-shooting-heroes-run-hide-fight/index.html|title=Again in the age of 'run, hide, fight,' student heroes thwart a school shooter|first=Eliott C.|last= McLaughlin|website=CNN}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/05/08/us/kendrick-castillo-denver-stem-shooting/index.html|title=This student died trying to stop the Colorado school shooter|author1=Nicole Chavez |author2=Scott McLean|website=CNN}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 28, 2019\n| Volsk, Saratov Region, Russia\n| Daniil Pulkin\n| \n| 1 injured\n| In the afternoon of May 28, the teenager came to school with a bag containing an axe and molotov cocktails inside. First, Pulkin attempted to burn the office of his former form mistress. After that, he hit a 6th grader girl in the head with an axe.\n|-\n| August 8, 2019\n| Montgomery, Alabama\n| Isaiah Johnson, 38\n| 0\n| 0\n| 38-year old Isaiah Johnson dropped his son off at Blount Elementary School, and then got into an argument with another father over a traffic dispute. He then discharged a firearm into the other father's vehicle.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wvtm13.com/article/2-arrested-after-road-rage-shooting-at-alabama-elementary-school/28647302|title=Back-to-school traffic leads to argument, shooting outside Alabama elementary school|first=The Associated|last=Press|date=August 8, 2019|website=WVTM}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.apr.org/post/mental-evaluation-sought-school-traffic-shooting-suspect|title=Mental evaluation sought for school traffic shooting suspect|first=Associated|last=Press|website=www.apr.org}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.montgomeryadvertiser.com/story/news/crime/2019/08/26/isaiah-johnson-charged-escape-after-blount-elementary-shooting/2121409001/|title=Father charged in Blount Elementary shooting re-arrested after escaping treatment facility|first=Melissa|last=Brown|website=The Montgomery Advertiser}}</ref>\n|-\n| August 30, 2019\n| Mobile, Alabama\n| Deangelo Dejuan Parnell, 17\n| 0\n| 10 injured\n| Parnell shot 9 people during a confrontation at a stadium where a high school football game was being played. A tenth person suffered a stroke.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/31/us/mobile-alabama-football-shooting.html|title=At Least 10 Shot at Alabama High School Football Game, Police Say|first=Derrick Bryson|last=Taylor|date=August 31, 2019|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 1, 2019\n| [[Kuopio]], Finland\n| Joel Marin, 25\n| 1 dead\n| 10 injured\n| [[Kuopio school stabbing]]\n|-\n| November 14, 2019 \n| Santa Clarita, California\n| Nathaniel Berhow, 16\n| 3 dead\n| 3 injured \n| [[Saugus High School shooting]]\n|-\n| November 14, 2019\n| [[Blagoveshchensk]], Russia\n| Daniil Zasorin, 19\n| 2 dead\n| 3 injured\n| After being told to leave the classroom twice, Zasorin returned with a pump-action shotgun and opened fire in the room, shooting victims at their desks. He committed suicide after being wounded in exchange of gunfire with police.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/russia-college-shooting-daniil-zasorin-attack-death-toll-latest-today-a9202526.html|title=Gunman opens fire in deadly Russian college attack after posting bizarre message online|date=14 November 2019|website=The Independent|accessdate=10 January 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[School bullying]]\n*[[School shooting]]\n*[[List of school-related attacks]]\n*[[List of school shootings in the United States]]\n*[[List of attacks related to primary schools]]\n*[[List of attacks related to post-secondary schools]]\n*[[List of rampage killers: School massacres]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist|refs=\n<ref name=note_a>Including death or injury of attacker(s), when applicable.</ref>}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181140/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence00-01.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2000\u20132001], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181216/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence02-03.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2002\u20132003], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181239/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence04-05.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2004\u20132005], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181347/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence06-07.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2006\u20132007], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181441/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence07-08.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2007\u20132008], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/2011